    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A family of stateless, application-level, request/response protocols that share a generic interface, extensible semantics, and self-descriptive messages to enable the retrieval of data on networks, especially of HTML documents via the Internet. HTTP is the foundation of data communication for the World Wide Web.</Note_Text>
